#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Māra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Sattavassānubandhasutta → sattavassasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | sattavassāni (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Sattavassānubandhasutta "
msgstr "24. Seven Years of Following "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn4.24:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn4.24:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre ajapālanigrodhe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā at the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.24:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena māro pāpimā sattavassāni bhagavantaṃ anubandho hoti otārāpekkho otāraṃ alabhamāno. "
msgstr "Now at that time Māra the Wicked had been following the Buddha for seven years hoping to find a vulnerability without success. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.24:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.123, pts2ed1.270, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.1"
msgid "“Sokāvatiṇṇo nu vanamhi jhāyasi, "
msgstr "“Are you overwhelmed by sorrow that you meditate in the forest? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.2"
msgid "Vittaṃ nu jīno uda patthayāno; "
msgstr "Have you lost a fortune, or do you long for one? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.3"
msgid "Āguṃ nu gāmasmimakāsi kiñci, "
msgstr "Or perhaps you’ve committed some crime in the village? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.4"
msgid "Kasmā janena na karosi sakkhiṃ; "
msgstr "Why don’t you get too close to people? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.5"
msgid "Sakkhī na sampajjati kenaci te”ti. "
msgstr "And why does no-one get close to you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.1"
msgid "“Sokassa mūlaṃ palikhāya sabbaṃ, "
msgstr "“I’ve dug out the root of sorrow completely. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.2"
msgid "Anāgu jhāyāmi asocamāno; "
msgstr "I practice absorption free of guilt or sorrow. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.3"
msgid "Chetvāna sabbaṃ bhavalobhajappaṃ, "
msgstr "I’ve cut off all greed and hunger for future lives. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.4"
msgid "Anāsavo jhāyāmi pamattabandhū”ti. "
msgstr "Undefiled, I practice absorption, O kinsman of the negligent!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ vadanti mama yidanti, "
msgstr "“The things they call ‘mine’, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.2"
msgid "ye vadanti mamanti ca; "
msgstr "and those who say ‘it’s mine’: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.3"
msgid "Ettha ce te mano atthi, "
msgstr "if your mind remains there, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.4"
msgid "na me samaṇa mokkhasī”ti. "
msgstr "you won’t escape me, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ vadanti na taṃ mayhaṃ, "
msgstr "“The things they speak of aren’t mine; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.2"
msgid "ye vadanti na te ahaṃ; "
msgstr "I’m not someone who speaks like that. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ pāpima jānāhi, "
msgstr "So know this, Wicked One: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.4"
msgid "na me maggampi dakkhasī”ti. "
msgstr "you won’t even see the path I take.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.271, sc6
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.1"
msgid "“Sace maggaṃ anubuddhaṃ, "
msgstr "“If you’ve discovered the path "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.2"
msgid "khemaṃ amatagāminaṃ; "
msgstr "that’s safe, and leads to the deathless, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.3"
msgid "Apehi gaccha tvameveko, "
msgstr "go and walk that path alone—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.4"
msgid "kimaññamanusāsasī”ti. "
msgstr "why teach it to anyone else?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.1"
msgid "“Amaccudheyyaṃ pucchanti, "
msgstr "“Those crossing to the far shore "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.2"
msgid "ye janā pāragāmino; "
msgstr "ask what’s beyond the domain of Death. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.3"
msgid "Tesāhaṃ puṭṭho akkhāmi, "
msgstr "When I’m asked, I explain to them "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.4"
msgid "yaṃ saccaṃ taṃ nirūpadhin”ti. "
msgstr "the truth without attachments.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.124, pts2ed1.272, sc8
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhante, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre pokkharaṇī. "
msgstr "“Sir, suppose there was a lotus pond not far from a town or village, "

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.2"
msgid "Tatrassa kakkaṭako. "
msgstr "and a crab lived there. "

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā kumārakā vā kumārikāyo vā tamhā gāmā vā nigamā vā nikkhamitvā yena sā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkameyyuṃ; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ kakkaṭakaṃ udakā uddharitvā thale patiṭṭhapeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Then several boys or girls would leave the town or village and go to the pond, where they’d pull out the crab and put it on dry land. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-tortoises-and-samadhi/3020
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.4"
msgid "Yaṃ yadeva hi so, bhante, kakkaṭako aḷaṃ abhininnāmeyya taṃ tadeva te kumārakā vā kumārikāyo vā kaṭṭhena vā kathalāya vā sañchindeyyuṃ sambhañjeyyuṃ sampalibhañjeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Whenever that crab extended a claw, those boys or girls would snap, crack, and break it off with a stick or a stone. "

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.5"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhante, kakkaṭako sabbehi aḷehi sañchinnehi sambhaggehi sampalibhaggehi abhabbo taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ otarituṃ. "
msgstr "And when that crab’s claws had all been snapped, cracked, and broken off it wouldn’t be able to return down into that lotus pond. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: bhante, yāni kānici visūkāyikāni → yāni visukāyikāni (bj, mr) | yāni kānici visukāyikāni (s1) | yānikānici visūkāyitāni (s2, s3) | yāni sukāyikāni (pts1)
#. VAR: vipphanditāni, sabbāni → kānici kānici sabbāni (bj, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.6"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhante, yāni kānici visūkāyikāni visevitāni vipphanditāni, sabbāni tāni bhagavatā sañchinnāni sambhaggāni sampalibhaggāni. "
msgstr "In the same way, sir, the Buddha has snapped, cracked, and broken off all my tricks, dodges, and evasions. "

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.7"
msgid "Abhabbo dānāhaṃ, bhante, puna bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamituṃ yadidaṃ otārāpekkho”ti. "
msgstr "Now I’m not able to approach the Buddha again in hopes of finding a vulnerability.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.8"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato santike imā nibbejanīyā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked recited these verses of disappointment in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.1"
msgid "“Medavaṇṇañca pāsāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "“A crow once circled a stone "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.2"
msgid "vāyaso anupariyagā; "
msgstr "that looked like a lump of fat. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.3"
msgid "Apettha muduṃ vindema, "
msgstr "‘Perhaps I’ll find something tender,’ it thought, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.4"
msgid "api assādanā siyā. "
msgstr "‘perhaps there’s something tasty.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.1"
msgid "Aladdhā tattha assādaṃ, "
msgstr "But it didn’t find anything tasty, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.2"
msgid "vāyasetto apakkame; "
msgstr "so the crow left that place. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.3"
msgid "Kākova selamāsajja, "
msgstr "Like the crow that pecked the stone, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.4"
msgid "nibbijjāpema gotamā”ti. "
msgstr "I leave Gotama disappointed.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
